&gt; characters from 
&gt; &gt; the US-ASCII [ISO646 &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5646#ref-ISO646"&gt;https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5646#ref-ISO646&lt;/a&gt;&gt;] 
&gt;
&gt; &gt; repertoire
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; From this, I would conclude that a string containing non-ASCII 
&gt; characters 
&gt; &gt; cannot be a &quot;language tag&quot; per BCP47 at all, and therefore cannot 
&gt; possibly match.
