&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AW9DxKYNfnt_wruxmd-_M1islS-MgsUVpaNBen-XvHk"&gt;https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AW9DxKYNfnt_wruxmd-_M1islS-MgsUVpaNBen-XvHk&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Summary
&gt;
&gt; This feature enables websites to support contextual biasing for speech
&gt; recognition by adding a recognition phrase list to the Web Speech API.
&gt; Developers can provide a list of phrases as well as updating them to apply
&gt; a bias to the speech recognition models in favor of those phrases. This
&gt; helps improve accuracy and relevance for domain-specific and personalized
&gt; speech recognition.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Blink component
&gt; Blink&gt;Speech
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3ESpeech%22"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3ESpeech%22&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
