&gt; On 2025-06-25 20:01, Slobodan Pejic wrote:
&gt;
&gt; But clearing data, can the user reset or delete this key in an intuitive
&gt;&gt; way?
&gt;&gt;
&gt; The browser bound keys are associated with their respective passkeys, so
&gt; users would need to delete the respective passkey. On Android, Chrome will
&gt; delete browser bound keys on startup when the respective passkey is no
&gt; longer available: A user deleting their passkey will result in Chrome
&gt; deleting the respective browser bound key. On desktop, if a passkey is
&gt; being deleted through Chrome then the respective browser bound key is
&gt; deleted at the same time, additionally Chrome will delete browser bound
&gt; keys for passkeys that have not been used for 9 months to cover any
&gt; unexpected cases where a passkey may have been deleted outside of Chrome.
&gt;
&gt; Additionally, deleting the Chrome App on Android (or removing the profile
&gt; from disk on Desktop) removes the association from a browser bound key to
&gt; its passkey. The browser bound key would not be available (and a different
&gt; browser bound key would be created as needed when paying).
&gt;
